main event: Two witnesses observed unidentified flying objects in Shelby, Montana on April 25, 1960.
interesting points: Witnesses reported a total of five sightings of the same object over a period of time., The objects were described as circular and emitted a strong white light., They appeared to move in a trail formation, changing speeds and directions rapidly., No specific details about the objects were available, as provided photographs were uninformative., The case remains classified as 'unidentified' by the Project Blue Book analysis.
